Terminalia . Apex of ventral median lobe pointed and apex of dorsal lobe rounded; ventral lobe distinctly longer than dorsal lobe. Spined region of internal sac slightly longer than basal unspined region, divided into 3 sections: first section about 1 / 2 length of unspined region, with long simple spines; second section slightly shorter than first section, with finger­shaped spines, and with a semicircular chitinous structure near third section; third section with a Y­shape chitinous structure near base and with no spines (
Fig. 9
). Eighth sternite parallel at sides, with an oval­shaped membrane area in middle and dense simple microspines on ventral surface; apex V­shaped, with dense setae (
Fig. 10
). Eighth tergite rounded or slightly emarginate at apex, with dense simple microspines and multibranched spines on dorsal surface (
Fig. 11
). Parameres 1 / 6 – 1 / 5 length of tegmen (
Fig. 12
). Ventral apodeme without inner process between arms, stem longer than arms (
Fig. 13
).

Ovipositor . Paraproct baculi extending from about basal 1 / 3 to coxite; proctiger baculus about as long as paraproct baculus and 2.9 length of dorsal baculus. Length of stylus slightly shorter than coxite width (
Fig. 14
).

Spermatheca . C­shaped, gradually narrowed towards base. Spermathecal gland arising from about basal 1 / 3 of spermatheca (
Fig. 15
).

Eighth sternite . Nearly square­shaped, width 1.3 as long as length; length of needle 2.5–2.6 length of eighth sternite (
Fig. 16
).
